-- Emerging Markets VIX Futures Begin Trading Next Week, CBOE Says
-- B y   J e f f   K e a r n s   a n d   N i n a   M e h t a
-- 2012-01-06T19:59:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-06/emerging-markets-vix-futures-begin-trading-next-week-cboe-says.html
Volatility futures linked to
emerging-markets stocks begin trading on the CBOE Futures
Exchange on Jan. 9, according to a statement from CBOE 
Holdings, which runs the largest U.S. equity options market.  The futures track the CBOE Emerging Markets ETF  Volatility
Index (VXEEM) , a gauge of options prices and expected price swings for
the iShares MSCI Emerging Markets exchange-traded fund. The
U.S.-listed ETF tracks 859 companies in 21 nations, from Samsung
Electronics Co. to China Mobile Ltd. to OAO Gazprom. Barclays
Plc is the lead market maker for the futures, CBOE said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
